<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AFC G-03902 - The Hood Dampening Cylinder, which Restrains the Hood during Opening and Closing, may Separate
        or Pull from the Hood Mounting Surface on 9900i and 9900ix Models Built Between April 19, 2001 and January 2,
        2002
    </stitle>
    <afc id="afc03902">
        <afcnum>G-03902</afcnum>
        <afcdate>April, 2003</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>FRONT END SHEET METAL</subjectfile>
        <subject>The Hood Dampening Cylinder, which Restrains the Hood during Opening and Closing, may Separate or Pull
            from the Hood Mounting Surface on 9900i and 9900ix Models Built Between April 19, 2001 and January 2, 2002
        </subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9900i
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>04/19/2001</startdate>
                        <enddate>01/02/2002</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9900ix
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>04/19/2001</startdate>
                        <enddate>01/02/2002</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>
                    <exhotlnk document="../afcs/AFC03902.pdf" bookname="AFC">Print ready (PDF file) copy of the AFC
                        letter
                    </exhotlnk>
                </para>
                <para>The hood dampening cylinder, which restrains the hood during opening and closing, may separate or
                    pull from the hood mounting surface on 9900i and 9900ix Models built between April 19, 2001 and
                    January 2, 2002. The SERVICE PROCEDURE provides the instructions to install a new design mounting
                    plate for the dampening cylinder bracket.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
