        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid possible property damage and/or personal injury, park the vehicle on a flat level
                        surface, set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the radiator grille.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To avoid damage to the hood, use an assistant to help support the hood during the next Step.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the hood dampening cylinder at the hood bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Provide a suitable support for the hood to rest on being careful to protect the hood
                    from contact damage (Figure 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f039011" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g039011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Support the Hood</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Note position of the hood dampening cylinder bracket.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The hood cylinder bracket will mount to the new reinforcement bracket with bolts to the
                            original hood mounting holes.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove hood dampening cylinder bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Scuff, clean and prep hood surface for adhesive (Figure 2).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f039022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g039022.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Scuff, Clean and Prep Hood Surface</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The "C" channel reinforcement plate is not symmetrical. When properly located, the dampening
                        cylinder bracket mounting bolts will align with the original mounting holes.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Trial fit the new "C" channel reinforcement, Part Number 3577407C1, and the dampening
                    cylinder bracket and mark location (Figure 3).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f039023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g039023A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Trial Fit New "C" Channel Reinforcement and Cylinder Bracket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Arrow indicates hole which will not be covered when the "C" channel reinforcement plate
                        is properly located.
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Position "C" channel 4.61 inches from edge as shown.</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Scuff and clean the inside of the "C" channel reinforcement plate and evenly apply Fusor
                    T20/T21 adhesive.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the "C" channel reinforcement to the previously marked area.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the dampening cylinder bracket to the "C" channel reinforcement . Install the
                    bolts and tighten to 15 Lbf-ft (20 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the hood dampening cylinder to the hood bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f039024" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g039024.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Reconnect Dampening Cylinder to Bracket</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the grille.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
